state.label: Danionella mirifica differs from its only congener D. translucida in having a more elongate body (body depth 12.2-14.8 % SL vs. 18.5- 24.4 % SL)
Danionella mirifica differs from its only congener D. translucida in having a more elongate body (body depth 12.2-14.8 % SL vs. 18.5- 24.4 % SL)
8 (4), 9 (13), or 10 (3), first two unbranched, last two not articulating with same pterygiophore
17 (1), 18 (12), 19 (6), or 20 (1), first two unbranched, last two not articulating with same pterygiophore
furcate with remnants of larval fin fold in front of dorsal and ventral margin extending anteriorly
all elements of the Weberian apparatus, including claustrum and scaphium

char.label: Single ventromedian row of large melanophores between pelvic fins and tips of cleithra (vs. paired ventral paramedian rows of smaller melanophores between pelvics and tips of cleithra)
Lacking scattered small melanophores on ventrolateral sides of abdomen (vs. presence of these melanophores)
Body elongate with short dorsal fin situated at posterior half of long anal fin
A window in body musculature present at lateral side of anterior gasbladder chamber, so that pigmented surface visible

Position of vent sexually dimorphic. Out of 57 specimens, 13 males with anus located between pelvics and 44 females with anus at various positions posterior to pelvics but not always at usual position just in front of anal fin. All females usually with postpelvic remnants of larval fin fold associated with anus.
Two of the three pectoral radials
Weberian apparatus highly sexually dimorphic with large transverse process of second vertebra in males bearing a large ventromedian flange confluent with outer arm of os suspensorium (Fig. 2)
